title: Washington State Department of Transportation, Highway Urban and Urbanized Areas, Washington, 2008
name: Washington State Department of Transportation, Highway Urban and Urbanized Areas, Washington, 2008
description:
Highway Urban Areas, as defined by the Federal Highway Administration, are depicted as polygons.
Purpose:

      The Federal Highway Administration (FHWA) requires a review of highway urban and urbanized areas after each decennial US Census. The Census Bureau determines boundaries for urbanized areas with 50,000 or more people. Highway urbanized areas must include all areas defined as urbanized by the Census bureau but can and usually do include area beyond the Census Bureau defined boundaries. For urban areas of 5,000 through 49,999 people, FHWA uses city limits or Census Designated Place boundaries, with some adjustments, as the minimum area. This data set is used for identification of Urban Areas and as a reference layer for geographic information systems at WSDOT.

author.source: Highways Urban and Urbanized Areas of Washington State
